


gtild(1)                       Scilab Function                       gtild(1)






NAME
  gtild - tilde operation

CALLING SEQUENCE
  [gt]=gtild(g)
  [at,bt,ct,dt]=gtild(a,b,c,[d])

PARAMETERS

  g         : linear system (syslin list) or g=g(s) (rational or polynomial)

  gt        : linear system (syslin list) (same as g)

DESCRIPTION
  gtild returns gtild(s) = g(-s)' (in transfer form or in state-space).

  g is any matrix (constant, polynomial, transfer matrix, or state-space
  representaion with possibly a polynomial D matrix).

EXAMPLE
  s=poly(0,'s');w=[1/s,s;2/(s+1),1];gtild(w)
  ss2tf(gtild(tf2ss(w)))

SEE ALSO
  syslin, horner































